Package: udpscope
Architecture: all
Depends: ${python3:Depends}, ${misc:Depends},
         python3-numpy,
         tcpdump,
         iproute2,
         docker.io (optional),
         tshark (optional)
Recommends: docker.io, tshark
Description: Professional UDP traffic analysis and diagnostics tool
 UDPScope is a network observability and diagnostics tool for UDP traffic
 analysis on Linux systems. It provides comprehensive monitoring, analysis,
 and reporting capabilities for system administrators to diagnose UDP-based
 applications and services.
 .
 Features include:
  * Multi-method capture (tcpdump, tshark, Docker introspection, ss)
  * Comprehensive traffic analysis and statistics
  * Network diagnostics and troubleshooting
  * Threat assessment and anomaly detection
  * Clean, enterprise-safe implementation

Package: python3-udpscope
Architecture: all
Depends: ${python3:Depends}, ${misc:Depends},
         python3-numpy
Description: Python 3 module for UDP traffic analysis and diagnostics
 This package contains the Python 3 module for UDPScope, allowing you to
 import and use UDPScope functionality in your Python applications.
 .
 This is the library package; install 'udpscope' for the command-line tool.